Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.75,0:00:07.65,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}Uncle Kogorō, Ran and I went to a Noh mask museum on the edge of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.22,0:00:16.20,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}because a letter warning of a plan to murder the owner of the museum had arrived at the Mouri Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.10,0:00:21.45,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\an8\blur3}The museum was closed, and in addition to the owner, Jisaburō Izumi,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.33,0:00:21.45,Signs,,0,0,0,,Jisaburō Izumi (65)\NNoh Mask Museum Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.62,0:00:24.83,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho Toba (28)\NJisaburō's Appointed Nurse
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:28.34,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tatsurō Seikanji (45)\NNoh Mask Museum Executive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.46,0:00:30.51,Signs,,0,0,0,,Moyono Mibu (38)\NNoh Mask Museum Accountant and Receptionist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.63,0:00:32.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,Seinosuke Nagata (60)\NNoh Mask Museum Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.17,0:00:37.18,Signs,,0,0,0,,Naruya Akaza (40)\NAcquaintance of Jisaburō's / Promoter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.98,0:00:24.83,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3\an8}his appointed nurse, Hatsuho Toba{\rHonorifics - Narr}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.31,0:00:32.92,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3\an8}museum staff members Tatsurō Seikanji{\rHonorifics - Narr}-san{\r}, Moyono Mibu{\rHonorifics - Narr}-san{\r} and Seinosuke Nagata{\rHonorifics - Narr}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.92,0:00:37.18,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3\an8}and Naruya Akaza{\rHonorifics - Narr}-san{\r}, who had come to talk to the owner, were also there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.45,0:00:44.73,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}While the owner was showing us around the museum, his life was endangered several times,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.14,0:00:48.55,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}but it was Akaza{\rHonorifics - Narr}-san{\r} who ultimately ended up dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.98,0:00:56.30,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}Ran and I found Moyono{\rHonorifics - Narr}-san{\r} to be suspicious and sneaked into the office to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.03,0:01:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to call the police quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.80,0:01:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought Mibu had already done so.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.40,0:01:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was just pretending.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.55,0:01:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.83,0:01:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move, Missy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.59,0:01:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't imagine that the three of us were working together, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.17,0:01:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait here until we've dealt with the curator.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.91,0:01:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that Nagata guy's in on it too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.23,0:01:32.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.19,0:01:36.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Curator Izumi is in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.54,0:01:43.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HAAAA00\t(0,4050,\c)}Seeking comprehensive answers, he clears all mysteries and codes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.59,0:01:45.53,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\t(0,1940,\c&H88AA00)}The three culprits hatch an ominous plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.53,0:01:47.24,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&H88AA00}Let's solve the murder mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.24,0:01:49.00,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&H88AA00)\t(0,1760,\c)}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.00,0:01:51.10,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\t(0,2100,\c&HAA00AA)}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.10,0:01:53.79,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HAA00AA\t(0,1600,\c&H0000FF)}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.65,0:03:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and fell asleep just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.75,0:04:02.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.37,0:04:04.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Missy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.32,0:04:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.87,0:04:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did they escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.05,0:04:19.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those brats!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.75,0:04:26.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:32.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, this woman's actually the daughter of the mask artist Kodō.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.74,0:04:37.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though her mother divorced him and went back to her maiden name, Mibu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.91,0:04:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.10,0:04:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't mind.\NIt's not like it's a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.41,0:04:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever he was in a good mood, Kodō would carve masks over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.74,0:04:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used to play there as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.47,0:05:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was furious when she heard that Akaza was selling her father's creations on the cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, this means that she had a motive to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.90,0:05:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't take that seriously, Mr. Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.03,0:05:17.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go and get some fresh tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.13,0:05:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.95,0:05:25.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Inspector's really taking his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.70,0:05:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go check the entrance hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.85,0:05:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's a very attentive girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.54,0:05:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what I'd do without her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.15,0:05:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like the weights weren't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.70,0:05:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's you. Too bad, you were so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.71,0:06:25.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? A vengeful spirit mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.53,0:06:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.00,0:06:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.31,0:06:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.53,0:06:40.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's enter through that small door there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.90,0:06:44.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn! It won't open!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.52,0:06:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The peg must be fastened.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.39,0:06:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Peg?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.25,0:06:49.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a little bolt for fastening sliding doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.05,0:06:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those brats!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Curator!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.26,0:07:05.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.22,0:07:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! Open this little door!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.26,0:07:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.80,0:07:11.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take the curator outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.40,0:07:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.18,0:07:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm opening it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.08,0:07:17.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.20,0:07:21.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the curator?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.56,0:07:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took him outside just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.58,0:07:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Moyono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.00,0:07:28.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went to get some tea a little while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.79,0:07:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,F-Fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.00,0:07:35.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it, how did that happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.29,0:07:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's get out of here!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.20,0:07:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? I can't open it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.51,0:07:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's use the small door!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.15,0:07:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our exit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.49,0:07:47.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there! There's a door!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, good thing you're here. Help me out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.98,0:07:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've got about 20 minutes until the fire brigade arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.67,0:08:19.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.03,0:08:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.38,0:08:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Noh theatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.99,0:08:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's an exit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.44,0:08:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire has already spread!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.85,0:08:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, over there!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.30,0:08:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A demoness mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.40,0:08:40.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that woman! Hey, come down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.53,0:08:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.32,0:08:47.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More importantly, how do we get out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.31,0:08:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ladder! If we climb up the ladder, we should be able to get outside through that small window.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.50,0:08:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That window up there...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.39,0:08:57.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just close your eyes and you'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.61,0:09:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.60,0:09:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is bad, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}. The next building's too far away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.40,0:09:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.56,0:09:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll use the ladder as a bridge!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.30,0:09:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A bridge?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.75,0:09:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, Dad!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.24,0:09:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so hard on your father...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.85,0:09:30.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All together now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.69,0:09:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We did it! This way we can reach the window via the ladder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.96,0:09:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't look. Don't look. Don't—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.41,0:09:49.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep your eyes closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.89,0:09:52.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a bit further, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.60,0:09:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it feels like we've suddenly come back to the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.25,0:10:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must have built this annex more recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.96,0:10:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, let's move! That woman was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.78,0:10:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's gotta be a way out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.48,0:10:10.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An internal phone?! Where's it coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.85,0:10:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes? Ah, Toba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. So you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.33,0:10:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I took the curator and went to the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.80,0:10:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire hasn't reached here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.25,0:10:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be careful! To be safe from that executive and that Mibu woman, you should stay hidden for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We informed the police, so it shouldn't be much lo—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.51,0:10:32.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.57,0:10:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.40,0:10:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Sis'?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.61,0:10:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is Moyono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s little sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:46.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, we should hurry. Something could happen to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.95,0:10:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's lying there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.25,0:10:53.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.25,0:11:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the executive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.86,0:11:02.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's the third victim!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.13,0:11:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.77,0:11:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the kitchen. Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.81,0:11:23.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn. We're too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.78,0:11:33.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.82,0:11:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.25,0:11:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew of the plan my sister and the others were hatching.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.80,0:11:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet in the end I had no choice but to kill her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.09,0:11:55.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stabbing my own sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:11:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a horrible sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.41,0:12:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.28,0:12:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She might have killed you instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.94,0:12:12.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Even though the curator'd been warned, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.84,0:12:15.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.60,0:12:19.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An iron skewer, and there's something floating there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.05,0:12:23.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.54,0:12:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.11,0:12:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naruya Akaza{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Tatsurō Seikanji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Seinosuke Nagata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and Moyono Mibu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} have all been confirmed dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.20,0:12:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Curator Izumi narrowly escaped death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.48,0:12:41.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.85,0:12:50.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't question him yet, but since the wound has the same shape as the chisel that Mibu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was holding,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.97,0:12:54.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we can conclude that she was the one to attack him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.57,0:12:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.40,0:12:57.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A chisel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.33,0:13:04.90,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Stop it, Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.72,0:13:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:10.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's how it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.20,0:13:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't manage to stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.34,0:13:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister bore a grudge against the curator.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.25,0:13:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he sold our father's creations cheaply overseas through Akaza{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.85,0:13:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what was your opinion of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.64,0:13:35.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister and I have different mothers and grew up separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.95,0:13:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the curator was very kind to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you wanted to protect him when you heard about the plan to murder him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.33,0:13:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. So I sent a letter to Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nbut I couldn't stop my sister's madness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.21,0:13:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was she also the one who killed her accomplices: the executive and the manager?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.68,0:14:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think so. She said that if the two of them died, she'd get all of the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.31,0:14:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.90,0:14:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.05,0:14:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I hadn't planned it, I nonetheless killed my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You grabbed a skewer from the kitchen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.07,0:14:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to protect the curator, but please...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.54,0:14:28.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that you killed Mibu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} remains unchanged, but it was a clear case of legitimate self-defence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.25,0:14:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll need to hear a few more details at the station later.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.95,0:14:33.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.14,0:14:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! You'll have to come, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.55,0:14:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.00,0:14:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, the case is already...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.12,0:14:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.20,0:14:49.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.64,0:14:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Far from being closed, the culprit is cackling with glee over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.10,0:14:57.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.59,0:15:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the victim here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.07,0:15:06.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first mystery was how Akaza{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.70,0:15:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did the culprit manage to poison the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.24,0:15:16.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ate a bit of cheese, Akaza{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ate the same cheese and died.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.65,0:15:22.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean the poison had been applied to Akaza{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s butter knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.59,0:15:29.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, seats were chosen freely at that time, so it was impossible to target someone specifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.98,0:15:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one way it could've been done.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.35,0:15:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the spoon that was used to take some cheese the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.98,0:15:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By applying poison only to the underside of the spoon, the cheese taken with the spoon would be fine,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.97,0:15:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but at the same time, the remaining cheese would be poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.49,0:15:55.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Akaza{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died, the spoon that had fallen to the ground was replaced with a clean spoon while no one was looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.25,0:16:02.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the trick would have been easy to see through if the spoon had remained the way it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.51,0:16:09.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one who could have done that was whoever cleaned the cheese off the curator's clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.89,0:16:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! You're the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.08,0:16:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real reason you sent me that warning was so you could use me as a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.18,0:16:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make me testify that the three villains died and you survived through legitimate self-defence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.69,0:16:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the fire confined me to the house for a while, you used the opportunity to kill everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.86,0:16:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it would have been problematic if I had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.54,0:16:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you let us see your face through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.92,0:16:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that demoness mask wasn't Moyono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.22,0:16:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.43,0:16:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the climax of the play was the call on the internal phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.85,0:16:54.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that point you had already stabbed the curator and killed your sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.23,0:16:57.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she shouted 'Stop it, Sis'!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.15,0:16:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was just an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.40,0:17:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be capable of something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.23,0:17:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister stabbed the curator with a chisel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.61,0:17:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't have the opportunity to grab a weapon like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.72,0:17:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.29,0:17:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true. Moyono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.68,0:17:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you tempted her to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inciting her to kill him with the tools that your father loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.20,0:17:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, you grabbed some skewers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.88,0:17:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Skewers aren't anything like a chisel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.85,0:17:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You killed your sister with a skewer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.84,0:17:36.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moyono Mibu was a bad person, but maybe she trusted her sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.80,0:17:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.82,0:17:42.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must have guessed that her younger sister was the one to send me that warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.58,0:17:45.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she would have considered you to be untrustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.42,0:17:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you went and killed the curator to convince her otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.20,0:17:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Moyono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} let down her guard as a result,\Nyou stabbed her with that skewer right from the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.50,0:18:01.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But the curator's wound was caused by a chisel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.70,0:18:05.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. That was your last fortification.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.87,0:18:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately for you, fatal evidence of your trick remained.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.58,0:18:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being the culprit, you were really quite busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.04,0:18:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just your bad luck that you didn't have time to get rid of the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.89,0:18:18.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan! Bring it over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.94,0:18:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.08,0:18:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.75,0:18:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what is this?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.73,0:18:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They look like simple wood chips.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.25,0:18:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to Uncle Kogorō, she made these herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.63,0:18:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A V-shape is carved into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.91,0:18:37.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the shape of the blade of a chisel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.87,0:18:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A chisel?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.04,0:18:43.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.20,0:18:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She brought two skewers with her from the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.72,0:18:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Combining the two skewers so the cross-section formed a V, she used these two wood chips to hold them in that shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.90,0:19:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she stabbed the curator with the resulting weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.69,0:19:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so, Miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.59,0:19:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I give up! I give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.24,0:19:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You win, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.33,0:19:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. That's Hatsuho Toba's special murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.31,0:19:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Making it look like a chisel the first time and then using only a single skewer the second time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.18,0:19:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Then it really was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.94,0:19:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep, I'm the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.60,0:19:42.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would you kill your own sister too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.07,0:19:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's obvious, isn't it?! She was the curator's lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.17,0:19:55.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While my mother and me were living in poverty, she was living in luxury using the curator's money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.43,0:19:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now she suddenly wants to avenge our father?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.26,0:19:59.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's bull.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.19,0:20:04.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bastard Akaza sold off valuable Noh masks on the curator's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And on top of that, he took after the curator and tried to make eyes at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.60,0:20:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Disgusting. This museum's just for show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.30,0:20:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Burning it down and building a park instead is a much better use of the space.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.80,0:20:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector! Sorry to have made you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.60,0:20:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The speech is over now. Go arrest me or whatever!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.97,0:20:30.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.43,0:20:32.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.95,0:20:37.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.11,0:20:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.09,0:20:44.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Curator Izumi has regained consciousness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.94,0:20:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.13,0:20:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he didn't kick the bucket after all.\NI thought his reaction had been lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.28,0:20:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The force of the stab sent the wheelchair into the pond and I didn't finish him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.40,0:20:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess my endgame still needs some work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.09,0:21:01.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.91,0:21:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curator wanted to give his thanks to the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.42,0:21:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that about, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.95,0:21:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I helped him out a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.94,0:21:17.70,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Say, Mr. Curator, if you wrapped a sturdy plaited cord like that around your body,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.70,0:21:21.08,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}wouldn't it give you some protection if something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.08,0:21:25.64,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see! Even more so if it's an {\i1}odoshi{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.64,0:21:28.53,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It'd probably be effective against sharp weapons, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:32.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.06,0:22:59.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case took a rather ironic turn, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.12,0:23:03.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the people who had planned to kill the curator ending up killed instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.37,0:23:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.48,0:23:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case left a rather bad aftertaste.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.75,0:23:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think that everyone involved was a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.90,0:23:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in any case, it's like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.40,0:23:21.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a murder case so apologising won't make it better.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.43,0:23:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you think you did something bad you should apologise.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.28,0:23:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the Noh masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.72,0:23:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if there's {\i1}Noh{\i0} excuse!{uso: "noumen nasai!" - you prolly get the reference. I think this was a good adaptation xD}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.39,0:23:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.72,0:23:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.24,0:23:42.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I was wondering what you were going to say and then it's something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.96,0:23:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why were these chocolate bars thrown away?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.79,0:23:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'And the lone survivor laughs loudly'.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.71,0:23:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: 'A Devilish Cycle'!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.72,0:24:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Chocolate bar!
